SIMPLE: wheeling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wheeling
<hw>Wheel"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of conveying anything, or traveling, on
wheels, or in a wheeled vehicle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act or practice of using a cycle;
cycling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Condition of a road or roads, which admits of
passing on wheels; <as>as, it is good <ex>wheeling</ex>, or bad
<ex>wheeling</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A turning, or circular movement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheelman</ent>⟦br⟧
